s is for students whose practice is strong enough to be introduced to Headstand and beyond. Focus is given to understand from within the principles of the body, breath and mind. Students are encouraged to built their home practice.\r\n\r\n<b>Restorative</b>\r\n\r\nThis class teaches and explores supported practice. This type of practice is inevitable in time of weakness and fatigue. It also gives us space to explore more subtle aspects of yoga practice; the breath and the mind.', 'Classes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-10 22:50:24', '2013-11-10 22:50:24', '', 37, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/37-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(89, 1, '2013-11-11 08:22:57', '2013-11-11 08:22:57', 'There is a world of useful information published online and in books about Iyengar yoga.<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Here are some links to sites and books which you may find useful. </span>\r\n\r\nAlthough most books can be easily bought online, it’s always worth scanning the health sections of second hand bookshops in the UK. Many of my books came this way.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_44.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-84" alt="Hanuman, the monkey god" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_44.png" width="910" height="492" /></a>\r\n<h3><strong>Iyengar Yoga</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yogacharya B.K.S. Iyengar\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> <a href="http://www.bksiyengar.com/modules/Iyoga/iyoga.htm">official website</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.yogamatters.com/product/productlist.aspx?tb=1&amp;aja=1&amp;page=1&amp;o=7&amp;i=12&amp;val=0&amp;term=&amp;p=0&amp;dep=505&amp;c=0&amp;man=0&amp;atr=&amp;fpr=0&amp;wsh=0">Books by the Iyengars</a><b> </b>sold in UK by yogamatters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Mira Mehta\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.yogicpath.com/">The Yogic Path</a> school of yoga in London</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.yogicpath.com/publications">Books by Mira Mehta</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b style="line-height: 1.5;">Ayurveda</b></h3>\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Books by </span><a style="line-height: 1.5;" href="http://ayurveda.com/ayurvedic_press/index.html">Dr. Vasant Lad</a><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Books by</span><b style="line-height: 1.5;"> </b><b style="line-height: 1.5;"><a style="line-height: 1.5;" href="http://www.drsvoboda.com/books.htm">Dr. Robert Svoboda</a></b>\r\n<h3><b style="line-height: 1.5;">Online yoga resources</b><b style="line-height: 1.5;"> 