(186, 1, '2013-12-02 15:55:35', '2013-12-02 15:55:35', '<h4><a href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_41.png"><img alt="Stick figure Yoga" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_41.png" /></a></h4>\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 22px;">Lunchtime Classes at Yoga Loft</span></h1>\r\n<em>1 - 2 pm</em>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 22px;"><em>every Monday, Wednesday, Thursday &amp; Friday</em></span>\r\n\r\nFor full details including free taster classes click <a title="Lunchtime Classes at Yogaloft" href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/yogaloft/">here</a>!\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.3;">Eastern Yoga Studio</span></h1>\r\n<h4><span style="font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.3;">Tuesdays </span>10:30am - 12:00</h4>\r\nBeginners/General\r\n\r\n<em><a title="Eastern Yoga Studio" href="http://www.easternyoga.co.uk">www.easternyoga.co.uk</a></em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Bristol City Yoga</h3>\r\n<h4>Wednesdays 10am - 11:30am</h4>\r\nGeneral/Level 1 - 2 - 3\r\n\r\n<em><a href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk/">www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk</a></em>\r\n\r\nStarts 8th January 2014\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Wednesday Pranayama Course</h3>\r\n<h3>7.30pm - 9pm</h3>\r\nBristol City Yoga: <em><a href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk/">www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk</a></em>\r\n\r\n15th January - 19th February 2014\r\n<div>This course will be introducing basic breath control techniques.</div>\r\n<div>Pranayama is a more subtle part of yoga practice, where one conditions the flow of breath by changing its the length and pace, and by introducing new patterns. Although classically practiced in seated posture, we will first introduce it in supine poses.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The breath is a gateway to the inside world. With awareness of breath, our consciousness spreads to more subtle parts of the body. This is not possible by focusing only on the physical body, as it initially happens in our asana practice.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>By freeing the breath with correct positioning of the body and introduction of various breathing techniques, the inner balance and energy is restored, hence the name <em>Pranayama</em>, which refers to the life energy of the body.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Practice of Pranayama is a great practice of mindfulness, as the mind is focused within on the flow and pattern of the breath. This gives us a sense of stillness and serenity.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>This course is meant for students who have been practicing yoga for some time and would like to deepen their practice by learning more about the breath. Previous Pranayama knowledge is not required.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>£55 for the course</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>To book: <a title="Contact" href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/contact/">drop me a line</a></div>\r\n<div>alternatively, you may contact BCY:</div>\r\n<div>phone: 0117 924 4414</div>\r\n<div>e-mail: info@bristolcityyoga.co.uk</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><span style="font-size: 72px; color: #ffffff;">C</span></div>', 'Classes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-02 15:55:35', '2013-12-02 15:55:35', '', 37, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/37-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
