as it initially happens in our asana practice.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>By freeing the breath with correct positioning of the body and introduction of various breathing techniques, the inner balance and energy is restored, hence the name <em>Pranayama</em>, which refers to the life energy of the body.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Practice of Pranayama is a great practice of mindfulness, as the mind is focused within on the flow and pattern of the breath. This gives us a sense of stillness and serenity.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>This course is meant for students who have been practicing yoga for some time and would like to deepen their practice by learning more about the breath. Previous Pranayama knowledge is not required.\r\n\r\n£55 for the course</div>\r\n\r\n<div>To book: <a title="Contact" href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/contact/">drop me a line</a></div>\r\n<div>alternatively, you may contact BCY:</div>\r\n<div>phone: 0117 924 4414</div>\r\n<div>e-mail: info@bristolcityyoga.co.uk</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><span style="font-size: 72px; color: #ffffff;">C</span></div>', 'Classes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-02 15:58:30', '2013-12-02 15:58:30', '', 37, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/37-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
