(220, 1, '2013-12-07 11:56:57', '2013-12-07 11:56:57', '<img class="size-full wp-image-246 alignleft" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; border: 10px solid black;" alt="EasternYoga" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/EasternYoga.jpg" width="135" height="135" /><span style="font-size: 28px;">Yoga Day at Eastern Yoga Studio</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 20px;"><strong>Sunday 6th April </strong><strong style="line-height: 1.5;"></strong><strong style="line-height: 1.5;">2014</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<strong><em><span style="line-height: 1.5;">10.30am - 4.30pm</span></em></strong>\r\n\r\n46 Greenbank Rd, Bristol BS5 6EY\r\n\r\nI''ll be teaching a yoga day consisting of asana workshop in the morning and pranayama and restorative class in the afternoon. The afternoon session will start with short talk on basic principals of yoga philosophy. There will be one hour lunch break half-way through.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Please bring a light lunch. Tea will be provided.</span>\r\n\r\nPrice: £45; Eastern Yoga Members and Concessions £40\r\n\r\nTo book your spot use the booking form below and hand in/send to me.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/YogaDayRegistrationForm.pdf">YogaDayRegistrationForm</a></strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n<iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d2485.4671504166654!2d-2.559428!3d51.467939!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x0%3A0x6b12ce2dbeca8a7c!2sEastern+Yoga!5e0!3m2!1sen!2suk!4v1395775132636" width="400" height="300" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe>', 'Yoga Day at Eastern Yoga', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'yoga-day', '', '', '2014-03-25 19:21:48', '2014-03-25 19:21:48', '', 37, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/?page_id=220', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(221, 1, '2013-12-07 11:56:57', '2013-12-07 11:56:57', 'Wednesday\r\n\r\n7.30pm - 9pm\r\nBristol City Yoga: www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk\r\n15th January - 19th February 2014\r\n\r\nThis course will be introducing basic breath control techniques.\r\nPranayama is a more subtle part of yoga practice, where one conditions the flow of breath by changing its the length and pace, and by introducing new patterns. Although classically practiced in seated posture, we will first introduce it in supine poses.\r\n\r\nThe breath is a gateway to the inside world. With awareness of breath, our consciousness spreads to more subtle parts of the body. This is not possible by focusing only on the physical body, as it initially happens in our asana practice.\r\n\r\nBy freeing the breath with correct positioning of the body and introduction of various breathing techniques, the inner balance and energy is restored, hence the name Pranayama, which refers to the life energy of the body.\r\n\r\nPractice of Pranayama is a great practice of mindfulness, as the mind is focused within on the flow and pattern of the breath. This gives us a sense of stillness and serenity.\r\n\r\nThis course is meant for students who have been practicing yoga for some time and would like to deepen their practice by learning more about the breath. Previous Pranayama knowledge is not required.\r\n£55 for the course\r\nTo book: drop me a line\r\nalternatively, you may contact BCY:\r\nphone: 0117 924 4414\r\ne-mail: info@bristolcityyoga.co.uk', 'Pranayama Course', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-07 11:56:57', '2013-12-07 11:56:57', '', 220, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
