(270, 1, '2013-12-22 08:57:46', '2013-12-22 08:57:46', '<h3><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-250" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="BCY-Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/BCY-Logo.jpg" width="124" height="85" />6 week Pranayama Course</h3>\r\n<address>Wednesdays 6 - 7.15pm</address> <strong>22nd January - 26th February 2014</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Bristol City Yoga</strong>\r\n<a href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk">www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk </a>\r\n<em>16 Backfields Lane, Bristol, BS2 8QW</em>\r\n\r\nThis course will be introducing basic breath control techniques.\r\nPranayama is a more subtle part of yoga practice, where one conditions the flow of breath by changing its the length and pace, and by introducing new patterns. Although classically practiced in seated posture, we will first introduce it in supine poses.\r\n\r\nThe breath is a gateway to the inside world. With awareness of breath, our consciousness spreads to more subtle parts of the body. This is not possible by focusing only on the physical body, as it initially happens in our asana practice.\r\n\r\nBy freeing the breath with correct positioning of the body and introduction of various breathing techniques, the inner balance and energy is restored, hence the name Pranayama, which refers to the life energy of the body.\r\n\r\nPractice of Pranayama is a great practice of mindfulness, as the mind is focused within on the flow and pattern of the breath. This gives us a sense of stillness and serenity.\r\n\r\nThis course is meant for students who have been practicing yoga for some time and would like to deepen their practice by learning more about the breath. Previous Pranayama knowledge is not required.\r\n\r\n£50 for the course\r\n<a title="Bristol City Yoga Pranayama Course" href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk/classes-and-courses/courses/pranayama-course/" target="_blank">Book your Pranayama course online</a>\r\nOr contact BCY:\r\nphone: 0117 924 4414\r\ne-mail: info@bristolcityyoga.co.uk', 'Pranayama Course', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-22 08:57:46', '2013-12-22 08:57:46', '', 220, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(271, 1, '2013-12-22 09:16:22', '2013-12-22 09:16:22', '<h3><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-250" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="BCY-Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/BCY-Logo.jpg" width="124" height="85" />General Class</h3>\r\n<address><span style="font-size: 24px;"><strong>Mondays 9.30am - 11am</strong></span></address><strong>Starting 6th January 2014\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Bristol City Yoga</strong>\r\n<a href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk">www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk </a>\r\n<em>16 Backfields Lane, Bristol, BS2 8QW</em>\r\n\r\nThis class is open to all levels.\r\n\r\nIt is a dynamic and well rounded class.  We also look at all the basic principals to assure your practice foundation is grounded through alignment and understanding of the base of the posture. All inverted poses are taught according to the level of students.\r\n\r\nRelaxation and breath awareness techniques are taught regularly.\r\n\r\nA perfect way to start your week!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>', 'Bristol City Yoga', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '218-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-22 09:16:22', '2013-12-22 09:16:22', '', 218, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/218-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(273, 1, '2014-01-04 15:37:54', '2014-01-04 15:37:54', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-201" style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" title="Yoga Loft Bristol" alt="YogaLoftLogoAddress" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/YogaLoftLogoAddress-e1386005646620.png" width="600" height="152" /><span style="font-size: 28px;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">New!!</span> Lunchtime Yoga Classes at Yoga Loft, Bristol </span><span style="font-size: 28px;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/snowflakeBlueText.png"><img class="alignright" style="margin: 10px 20px;" title="Free Classes at Yogaloft, Bristol" alt="snowflakeBlueText" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/snowflakeBlueText.png" width="200" height="194" /></a></span>    1 - 2 pm daily\r\n<blockquote><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Free</span> Taster Classes!</strong>\r\n\r\n6th, 8th, 9th &amp; 10th January 2014\r\n\r\n1-2pm\r\n\r\nAll are Welcome!</blockquote>\r\n<iframe src="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1gCiYj1c7-gWfO1qQcvzvKTTvSDlBjqlG941JdGViXSA/viewform?embedded=true" height="850" width="760" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0"></iframe>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><em>*Limited to 10 students per class. First come first served basis.</em></span></p>\r\n<strong>Four new lunchtime classes at Yoga Loft Bristol from 6th January 2014!</strong>\r\n<h4>Monday - Foundation</h4>\r\n<em>1 - 2pm</em>\r\nStep by step introduction to the basic yoga postures. Perfect for yoga novices or those who like to brush up on yoga foundation in this progressively structured class.\r\n<h4>Wednesday - General</h4>\r\n<em>1 - 2pm</em>\r\nThis is a class for all levels from beginners to improvers. We will be focusing on different postures every week and basic breathing techniques will also be taught.\r\n<h4>Thursday - Beginners</h4>\r\n<em>1 - 2pm</em>\r\nDynamic class suitable for those with little or no experience in yoga. All basic yoga postures will be taught including shoulder stand and relaxation.\r\n<h4>Friday - Restorative</h4>\r\n<em>1 - 2pm</em>\r\nThis is a slower pace class suitable for all levels. Poses will be practised supported to help the body recover at the end of the week. This type of practice helps us prolong the timing in the poses and deepen the experience. More attention is given to the breath and basic breathing exercises will be taught regularly in this class.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Classes are suitable for all, no previous yoga experience needed!</span>\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 24px;">Prices from January</span></h1>\r\n<h4>1 hour Lunchtime Class</h4>\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 24px;"><img class="alignright  wp-image-172" style="margin: 10px;" title="£49 for 10 classes" alt="£49 for 10 Classes" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/49for10circle-300x300.png" width="180" height="180" /></span></h1>\r\n<span style="color: #ff0000;"><em>*New Student Offer!</em></span>\r\n10-class Yogacard - £49 for 6 weeks\r\n\r\n10-class Yogacard - £70 for 12 weeks\r\n\r\nDrop-in - £8\r\n<h4>1.5 hour Evening classes</h4>\r\n10-class Yogacard - £90 for 12 weeks\r\nDrop-in - £10\r\n\r\n<a title="Coming Soon!">View full Yoga Loft Timetable here!</a>\r\n\r\nYoga Loft is a fully equipped studio at Queen Square, Bristol\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-181 alignleft" style="margin-right: 20px; margin-left: 20px;" title="Osteopaths" alt="Osteopaths Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Osteopaths-Logo.png" width="38" height="24" />Osteopaths, 57 Queen Charlotte Street, Bristol BS1 4HQ\r\n<iframe src="https://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF8&amp;cid=3098133523227739122&amp;gl=GB&amp;hl=en&amp;t=m&amp;ll=51.451533,-2.594211&amp;spn=0.05,0.05&amp;z=16&amp;&amp;iwloc=near&amp;