(274, 1, '2013-11-18 15:38:48', '2013-11-18 15:38:48', '''<em>Yog Dīksha</em>'' roughly translates to Initiation into Yoga. This is a space for sharing the traditional teachings. The word Yoga may be interpreted in several different ways. It can be understood as ''union'' or to be one with the creation. It can also be thought of as tying together the various inclinations of the mind. Yoga is an ancient Indian school of thought, that provides a unique point of view into the workings of the world by understanding our own selves better.\r\n\r\nThe word Yoga, however, and especially in the West, has been overused and misused and has come to mean a mere shadow of its original intent. The use of the word <em>''Yog''</em> tries to distance itself from what has come to be understood as merely physical. Both words however, mean the same, and have been used interchangeably throughout the website.\r\n\r\n<i>Explore further: </i><i><a title="Yoga Sutras" href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/yoga-sutras/">The Yoga Sūtras of Patañjali</a></i>', 'Welcome', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'welcome', '', '', '2014-01-04 15:45:27', '2014-01-04 15:45:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/?p=274', 0, 'post', '', 0),
