(370, 1, '2014-03-18 13:52:17', '2014-03-18 13:52:17', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-201" style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" title="Yoga Loft Bristol" alt="YogaLoftLogoAddress" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/YogaLoftLogoAddress-e1386005646620.png" width="600" height="152" />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 28px;"><span style="color: #ff0000;">New!</span> Evening Yoga Class at Yoga Loft, Bristol </span>\r\n\r\nI''m taking over from Juliet, who is moving out of Bristol, the Thursday evening class. I''ll be teaching it from 27th March 2014!\r\n<h3>Thursday - General</h3>\r\n<strong><em>6 - 7.30pm</em></strong>\r\nThis class has been running for a long time and I''m looking forward to be teaching it. It''s a well rounded class suitable for all.\r\n\r\n<strong>Drop-in Rate</strong> - per class: £10\r\n\r\n<strong>Regulars Yogacard</strong> - 10 classes/ 12 weeks: £90 (Also Lunchtime ''Regulars Yogacard'' can be used with £2 supplement)\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 28px;">Lunchtime Yoga Classes at Yoga Loft, Bristol </span>\r\n\r\nI''m teaching 4 new lunchtime classes at Yogaloft: every Mon, Wed, Thu &amp; Fri 1 - 2pm\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="font-family: Bitter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.3;">Monday - Beginners </span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>1 - 2pm</em></strong>\r\nStep by step introduction to the basic yoga postures. Perfect for yoga novices or those who like to brush up on yoga foundation in this progressively structured class. All standing poses will be practiced regularly and you will learn to do Shoulder Stand and variations here. All other groups of poses will be also introduced.\r\n<h4>Wednesday - General</h4>\r\n<strong><em>1 - 2pm</em></strong>\r\nThis is a class for all levels from beginners to improvers. We will be focusing on different postures every week and basic breathing techniques will also be taught.\r\n<h4>Thursday - General</h4>\r\n<strong><em>1 - 2pm</em></strong>\r\nDynamic class suitable for all. All basic yoga postures will be taught including shoulder stand and relaxation.\r\n<h4>Friday - Restorative</h4>\r\n<strong><em>1 - 2pm</em></strong>\r\nThis is a slower pace class suitable for all levels. Poses will be practised aimed at helping the body recover at the end of the week. The timing in the poses is prolonged for a deeper experience. More attention is given to the breath and basic breathing exercises will be taught regularly in this class.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Classes are suitable for all, no previous yoga experience needed!</span>\r\n<h3>Just Drop In!</h3>\r\nAll classes are drop in, but if you have any questions or need to tell us something, please use <a title="Contact" href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/contact/">this form</a>.\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 24px;">Prices</span></h1>\r\n<h4>1 hour Lunchtime Class</h4>\r\n<h4><img class="wp-image-360 alignleft" style="border: 1px solid black; margin-left: 5px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="Yoga Card" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/YogaCard-small.jpg" width="217" height="138" /></h4>\r\n<strong>Frequent Yogacard</strong> - 10 classes/ 6 weeks: £49\r\n\r\n<strong>Regulars Yogacard</strong> - 10 classes/ 12 weeks: £70\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright  wp-image-172" style="margin: 10px;" title="£49 for 10 classes" alt="£49 for 10 Classes" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/49for10circle-300x300.png" width="144" height="144" /><strong>Drop-in Rate</strong> - per class: £8\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>About The Teacher</h3>\r\nAndrea is an experienced Iyengar Yoga teacher with a friendly and compassionate teaching style. She places great focus on attention to detail and the individual needs of her students. <a title="About Me" href="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/about-me/"><em>Read more..</em></a>\r\n<h3>Yoga Loft</h3>\r\n<h4><a title="Time Table Yoga Loft (new window)" href="http://www.southbristolosteopaths.co.uk/yoga-loft/the-prices.html" target="_blank"><span style="font-family: ''Source Sans Pro'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: medium;"><span style="line-height: 1.5;">View full Yoga Loft Timetable</span></span></a></h4>\r\nYoga Loft is a fully equipped studio at Queen Square, Bristol\r\n\r\n<img class="wp-image-181 alignnone" style="margin-right: 20px; margin-left: 20px;" title="Osteopaths" alt="Osteopaths Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Osteopaths-Logo.png" width="38" height="24" />Osteopaths, 57 Queen Charlotte Street, Bristol BS1 4HQ\r\n<iframe src="https://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF8&amp;cid=3098133523227739122&amp;gl=GB&amp;hl=en&amp;t=m&amp;ll=51.451533,-2.594211&amp;spn=0.05,0.05&amp;z=16&amp;&amp;iwloc=near&amp;output=embed" height="350" width="600" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>', 'Yoga Loft', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-18 13:52:17', '2014-03-18 13:52:17', '', 154, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/154-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(371, 1, '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '<h3><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-250" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="BCY-Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/BCY-Logo.jpg" width="124" height="85" />6 week Pranayama Course</h3>\r\n<address>Wednesdays 6 - 7.15pm</address> <strong>22nd January - 26th February 2014</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Bristol City Yoga</strong>\r\n<a href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk">www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk </a>\r\n<em>16 Backfields Lane, Bristol, BS2 8QW</em>\r\n\r\nThis course will be introducing basic breath control techniques.\r\nPranayama is a more subtle part of yoga practice, where one conditions the flow of breath by changing its the length and pace, and by introducing new patterns. Although classically practiced in seated posture, we will first introduce it in supine poses.\r\n\r\nThe breath is a gateway to the inside world. With awareness of breath, our consciousness spreads to more subtle parts of the body. This is not possible by focusing only on the physical body, as it initially happens in our asana practice.\r\n\r\nBy freeing the breath with correct positioning of the body and introduction of various breathing techniques, the inner balance and energy is restored, hence the name Pranayama, which refers to the life energy of the body.\r\n\r\nPractice of Pranayama is a great practice of mindfulness, as the mind is focused within on the flow and pattern of the breath. This gives us a sense of stillness and serenity.\r\n\r\nThis course is meant for students who have been practicing yoga for some time and would like to deepen their practice by learning more about the breath. Previous Pranayama knowledge is not required.\r\n\r\n£50 for the course\r\n<a title="Bristol City Yoga Pranayama Course" href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk/classes-and-courses/courses/pranayama-course/" target="_blank">Book your Pranayama course online</a>\r\nOr contact BCY:\r\nphone: 0117 924 4414\r\ne-mail: info@bristolcityyoga.co.uk', 'Yoga Day ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '', 220, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
