(404, 1, '2015-05-30 09:33:56', '2015-05-30 09:33:56', '<h2>Andrea Ray</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-151" style="margin-left: 25px; margin-right: 25px;" title="Andrea Ray" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Andrea-profileshoot-640-300x200.jpg" alt="Andrea profile" width="300" height="200" />I was introduced to Iyengar Yoga at an early age, about 20 years ago. I have come a long way since and have now been teaching many public classes for the past 8 years. I hold Junior Intermediate Teaching Level 3 qualification.\r\n\r\nMore than just the physical postures, yoga as a philosophy has always fascinated me. I feel very fortunate to have access to the never-ageing wisdom through the work of Patanjali’s Yogasutras and through more recent works of BKS Iyengar that has brought Yoga to the world’s consciousness.\r\n\r\nMy daily practice is focused on finding deeper connection with myself and reconnecting with the core of being. I’ve been fortunate to study under many wise and knowledgeable teachers from all around the world as well as with the Iyengar family.\r\n\r\nTeaching is a great joy. I enjoy teaching students new to yoga and seeing the positive changes it brings. I also enjoy working with experienced students a on much more subtle level to help them find the teacher within them. Dealing with my own obstacles on the path has made me more compassionate and understanding.\r\n\r\nIyengar yoga offers endless variety of approaches and I focus on using the appropriate tools according to the need of students, and the cycle of nature.\r\n\r\nI''ve recently moved back to London and I''m currently on maternity leave. I''ll be looking to teach again in 2015 around West London. In the recent past, I''ve been teaching in Bristol and around Central and North London.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;"><span style="line-height: 1.5;">You can also </span><a style="line-height: 1.5;" title="My Iyengar Yoga Profile" href="https://www.iyengaryoga.org.uk/profile/4796" target="_blank">visit my Profile</a><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> on the Iyengar Yoga Association UK website.</span></span>', 'About Me', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-30 09:33:56', '2015-05-30 09:33:56', '', 4, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(405, 1, '2015-05-30 09:38:47', '2015-05-30 09:38:47', '<h4><img src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_41.png" alt="Stick figure Yoga" width="910" height="492" /></h4>\r\n<h3>General public classes</h3>\r\nI''m currently based in Ealing, West London.  I''m looking to start teaching general classes in this area soon.\r\n<h3><span style="font-family: Bitter, Georgia, serif; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.3;">Private classes</span></h3>\r\nOne-to-one classes have the benefit of focusing directly on your specific needs and goals. It is a great way to get to know and understand your body whilst addressing your particular tendencies and weak areas. One-to-one is the traditional way of teaching which allows the student to practice exactly according to their personal needs under close guidance of an experienced teacher.\r\n\r\nFamily class or a small group class can also be arranged.\r\n\r\nThese classes can be offered at the comfort of your home and necessary equipment will need to be available.\r\n<h3>Corporate classes</h3>\r\nCorporate yoga classes are a fantastic way to boost the work morale and well being of employees. Yoga helps build strength, stamina, balance and flexibility, whilst creating a balanced mental state with strong sense of vitality and health.\r\n\r\nI offer lunchtime and evening classes on-site. Suitable space will need to be arranged to accommodate all the participants. Basic yoga equipment will also need to be provided.\r\n\r\n<strong>Private and corporate classes are priced at £60 for 1 hour class or £45 for 45 min class.</strong>\r\n\r\n<!--[subpage_peek]-->', 'Classes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-30 09:38:47', '2015-05-30 09:38:47', '', 37, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/37-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
